<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ920121-0074</DOCNO><DOCID>920121-0074.</DOCID><HL>   Letters to the Editor:   Value-Neutral Xmas</HL><DATE>01/21/92</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A21</SO><LP>   &quot;Now Sing Along: O Solstice Tree, O Solstice Tree . . . &quot;(page one, Dec. 23) is value-neutral, presenting Christian,Wiccan and athiest positions. Unfortunately, your style guideis apparently not equally value-neutral. The use of the terms&quot;B.C.&quot; and &quot;A.D.&quot; assume that Jesus was a Christ and Lord,respectively. At the very least, when writing aboutalternatives to Christian practices you could recognize thisimplicit bias, and use the accepted terms &quot;B.C.E.&quot; (Beforethe Common Era) and &quot;C.E.&quot; (Common Era) instead.   Andrew Marc Greene</LP><TEXT>   Brookline, Mass.</TEXT></DOC>